quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,38,"We said, “Descend from it, all together. Then whenever any guidance comes to you from Me, then whoever follows My guidance—then <span class=""h"">no fear<sup foot_note=""79591"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">shall be</span>upon them{2}nor shall they grieve.",footnotes:2:A grammatical shift from singular to plural.
  2,39,"But those who have denied and disbelieved in Our signs—those are the fellows of the Fire; therein they abide.”"
  2,40,"O Children of Israel, “Remember My blessing which I blessed you with and fulfill your<i class=""s"">(part of the) </i>covenant so that I fulfill My<i class=""s"">(part of the) </i>covenant, and fear Me alone."
  2,41,"And believe<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>in what I have sent down, confirming what is with you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>. And do not be the first denier{1}of it, and do not purchase, inexchange for My revelations, a small price, and be mindful of Me alone.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from plural to singular.
  2,42,"And do not mix truth with falsehood, and do not conceal the truth while you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>know."
  2,43,"And establish the prayer, and bring{1}the purifying charity{2}, and bow down with the ones bowing down.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.|2:The Arabic word used is zakāt, which denotes purification and growth.
  2,44,"Do you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>command mankind to virtue and forget yourselves, even though you read the Scripture? Do you not reason?"
  2,45,"And seek<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>help through patience and prayer, and it is indeed a great burden except for the reverent"
  2,46,"who are certain that they shall meet their Lord and that to Him they will return."
  2,47,"O Children of Israel, remember My blessing with which I blessed you, and that I favored you over all communities."
  2,48,"And be mindful of a day{1}when no self avails another in anything, nor is any intercession accepted on its behalf, nor is any ransom taken from it, nor are they<a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a> supported.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘protect yourselves against a day’.
